author: Slidebean
description:
Fraudsters are using rogue cell towers to send 100,000 scam texts at once—already spotted in the UK, New Zealand, and Vietnam. 
SMS is starting to feel like AOL email scams all over again.

Full breakdown on The Slidebean Stand-Up—now streaming on Spotify, Apple Podcasts, or wherever you get your shows
title: Scammers Build Fake Cell Towers to Blast Texts
